<text layer="alpha" matrix="1 0 0 1 -204.56 62.0254" transformations="translations" pos="256 416" stroke="black" type="label" width="287.4" height="19.3928" depth="5.404" valign="baseline">Array to sort: bifgajedhc</text>
<text layer="beta" transformations="translations" pos="48 432" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="656" height="36.8592" depth="22.96" valign="top">Notation: $[x:y]$ is the set of elements \\between $x$ and $y$, including $x$ and $y$.</text>
<text layer="gamma" transformations="translations" pos="48 336" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="656" height="20.9244" depth="6.972" valign="top">Example: $[b:f] = \{b,c,d,f\}$, $[g:e] = \{e,f,g\}$</text>
<text layer="delta" transformations="translations" pos="48 256" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="656" height="36.8592" depth="22.96" valign="top">\textbf{Lemma.} $A_{x,y} = 1$ if and only if among the elements of $[x:y]$, element $x$ comes first in the input array.</text>
</page>
