<text layer="epsilon" transformations="translations" pos="55.5015 276.188" stroke="black" type="label" width="279.605" height="17.9352" depth="5.976" valign="baseline" size="small">{ \color{blue}$\{c,d,e,f\}$} stays together...</text>
<text layer="theta" matrix="1 0 0 1 33.1378 15.9149" transformations="translations" pos="29.3013 241.912" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="369.07" height="30.9384" depth="19.008" valign="top" size="small">... until one of its elements\\ is selected as pivot</text>
<text layer="iota" transformations="translations" pos="11.1288 189.022" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="410.618" height="32.0256" depth="20.112" valign="top" size="small">If the pivot is $f$, it will be compared to $c$,\\
and $A_{f,c} = 1$.</text>
<text layer="kappa" matrix="1 0 0 1 0.789718 -64.7107" transformations="translations" pos="11.1288 189.022" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="410.618" height="32.0256" depth="20.112" valign="top" size="small">Otherwise, $f$ and $c$ will now be separated and $A_{f,c} = 0$.</text>
</page>
