<text layer="alpha" matrix="1 0 0 1 0 240" transformations="translations" pos="48 256" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="656" height="36.8592" depth="22.96" valign="top">\textbf{Lemma.} $A_{x,y} = 1$ if and only if among the elements of $[x:y]$, element $x$ comes first in the input array.</text>
<text layer="beta" transformations="translations" pos="48 384" stroke="black" type="label" width="87.3488" height="20.9216" depth="7.98" valign="baseline" style="math">\mathbf{E}[A_{f,c}]</text>
<text layer="gamma" matrix="1 0 0 1 96 0" transformations="translations" pos="48 384" stroke="black" type="label" width="442.204" height="20.9244" depth="6.972" valign="baseline" style="math"> = \textnormal{Pr} [f \textnormal{ comes first among } 
\{c,d,e,f\}]</text>
<text layer="delta" matrix="1 0 0 1 -80 0" transformations="translations" pos="432 336" stroke="black" type="label" width="356.796" height="17.9352" depth="5.976" valign="baseline" size="small">(in a randomly shuffled input array)</text>
<text layer="epsilon" matrix="1 0 0 1 96 -96" transformations="translations" pos="48 384" stroke="black" type="label" width="55.0088" height="23.5816" depth="9.604" valign="baseline">$ = \frac{1}{4}$.</text>
<text layer="zeta" transformations="translations" pos="48 240" stroke="black" type="label" width="121.965" height="19.3928" depth="5.404" valign="baseline">In general:</text>
<text matrix="1 0 0 1 0 -192" transformations="translations" pos="48 384" stroke="black" type="label" width="190.926" height="23.5648" depth="14.504" valign="baseline" style="math">\mathbf{E}[A_{x,y}] = \frac{1}{ |[x:y]|}</text>
</page>
<page>
